{"body": "You say \"In particular, there is no point in saying that xhr? returns 0, it's of no use to the user, and it is a detail we do not need to commit to.\"\r\n\r\nThis is demonstrably false. See the thread for #5329, where at least one person reports it causing bugs in their app.\r\n\r\nI listed the core library documents to make a point: when the core library departs from true/false, it documents what it returns (and thus implicitly why it diverged from the default).\r\n\r\nFinally, I'll bet most readers of the doc won't read \"```true```\" and \"true\" as having distinct meanings.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4682840", "created_at": "2012-03-25T17:04:33Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5572#issuecomment-4682840", "updated_at": "2012-03-25T17:06:29Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5572, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Empact", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/b4493ae064e6e2841f376fd1dc12b7ba?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fbaed9f51d412c2514ee46a0942138ad6.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/received_events", "gravatar_id": "b4493ae064e6e2841f376fd1dc12b7ba", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "Empact", "type": "User", "id": 5470, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Empact/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523815d4bd3543c15100dd98"}, "id": 4682840, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5572"}
